Lineage of Jesus Christ
The Book of the Birth of Jesus the Messiah, son of David, son of Abraham:
Ibrahim was the son of Isaac. Isaac was the son of Jacob. Jacob was the son of Judah and his brothers.
And Judah was the son of Perez and Zerah, who were the sons of Tamar. Perez was the son of Hezron. Hezron was the son of Aram.
And Aram was the son of Carmi. And Carmi was the son of Nachshon. And Nachshon was the son of Salmon.
And Salmon was the son of Boaz, who was the son of Obed, who was the son of Jesse.
Absalom was the son of David the king. David the king was the son of Solomon from Uriah's wife.
Solomon was born to Rehoboam. Rehoboam was born to Abia. Abia was born to Asa.
And Josaphat was born to Ahaz. And Ahaz was born to Uzziah. And Uzziah was born to Joram.
And Zerah was the son of Yoash. And Yoash was the son of Ahaz. And Ahaz was the son of Hezekiah.
Jeconiah was the son of Manes. Manes was the son of Ammon. Ammon was the son of Josiah.
Josiah was born to Jechoniah and his brothers in Babylon.
And after Nebuchadnezzar, King Belshazzar was born. Belshazzar was the son of Zedekiah.
Zaribabel was the son of Abihud. Abihud was the son of Aliyqim. Aliyqim was the son of Azur.
Wazir son of Saadouk. Saadouk son of Akhem. Akhem son of Aliod.
And Eliud was born to Eliazar. And Eliazar was born to Mahan. And Mahan was born to Jacob.
Jacob was the son of Joseph, the son of Mary, from whom Jesus, called the Messiah, was born.
From Abraham to David, fourteen generations; from David to the Babylonian exile, fourteen generations; from the Babylonian exile to Christ, fourteen generations. The birth of Jesus Christ.
As for the birth of Jesus the Messiah, it was like this: when Mary, his mother, was engaged to Joseph, before they had come together, she received the Holy Spirit.
Joseph was her husband, as he was, and did not wish to make her known; he intended to release her secretly.
But as he pondered these matters, the Lord's angel appeared to him in a dream and said: "O Joseph, son of David, do not be afraid to take Mary as your wife. For the one who conceived in her is from the Holy Spirit."
And she bore a son and named him Jesus, for He will deliver His people from their sins.
All of this was to fulfill what God said to the Prophet, who said:
Behold, the virgin shall conceive and bear a son, and they shall call his name Emmanuel," which means "God with us."
And when Joseph awoke from his sleep, he did exactly as the angel of God had commanded him, and took his wife.
And she did not know it until she gave birth to her firstborn son. She named him Jesus.
