Then Jesus came and touched them, saying, "Stand up, and do not be afraid."
They raised their eyes and saw no one except Jesus alone.
And as they were descending from the mountain, Jesus said to them: "Do not tell anyone what you have seen until the Son of Man rises from the dead."
And his disciples asked him, saying: "Why do the scribes say that Elijah must come first?"
Then Jesus answered them and said: "Elijah will come first and restore all things."
But I tell you: Elijah has come and they did not recognize him, but they have done whatever they wished to him. So will the Son of Man suffer among them too.
At that time the disciples understood that He had said to them about John the Baptist: "He healed a boy with a demon."
And when they came to the gathering, a man lying on his side approached him.
And they said: "O Lord, have mercy on my son, for he suffers greatly, and often falls into fire and often into water."
And he brought him to your disciples, and they were not able to heal him.
Then Jesus answered and said: "O unbeliefful generation, rebellious ones, how long shall I be with you? How long shall I bear with you? Bring him here to me!"
Jesus rebuked him, and the demon came out of him. From that hour the boy was healed.
Then the disciples approached Jesus privately and said: "Why couldn't we drive it out?"
Then Jesus said to them: "Because of your lack of faith. Truly I tell you, if you had faith as small as a mustard seed, you would say to this mountain, 'Move from here to there,' and it would move. Nothing would be impossible to you."
As for this group, they do not emerge except through prayer and fasting.
And as they were hesitating in Galilee, Jesus said to them: "The Son of Man will be delivered into the hands of men."
They will kill him, and on the third day he will rise again." So they were greatly saddened. The Temple tax
And when they came to Kfar Nahum, those who took the two drams went forward to Peter and said: "Does not your teacher fulfill the two drams?"
He said, "Yes." And as he entered the house, Jesus said to him, "Simon, what do you think? From whom do kings of the earth take taxes or tolls—from their own people or from foreigners?"
Peter said to him, "From foreigners." Jesus said to him, "If the children are free."
But so that we may not find them, go to the sea and cast a net; take the first fish that appears, open it, and you will find a hiding place; take it and give it to them, both for me and for you.
